<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1471,1927]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,335,1867,1891]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[843,977,1867,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glaucocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scrotiformis">
<emphasis box="[843,977,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">scrotiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= baggy, in reference to the shape of the corpus bursae in the female genitalia.
</paragraph>
